        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:23PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Laurel Hills, or near
Columbus, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Columbus, Hamilton, Talbotton, Manchester, Pine Mountain, Waverly
Hall, Warm Springs, Pine Mountain-Callaway Gardens, Bibb City,
Upatoi, Shiloh, Ellerslie, Goat Rock Lake, Laurel Hills, Green Island
Hills, Cataula, Columbus Metropolitan Airport, Baughville, Rose Hill,
and Flint Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
